   <head>Ad Lectorem in laudem
Authoris.</head>
   <l>PVllulat en stirpi similis speciofa propago</l>
   <l>Aureolus{que} nouo reuirescit ramus amoris</l>
   <l>Vere: (tuo verè iam VERE dicandus honori):</l>
   <l>Ista salus Iuueni, Comiti <gap reason="illegible" resp="#tech" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>it gloria nosse</l>
   <l>Accepisse decus: Comites vbi passibus aequis</l>
   <l>Ales amor virtus{que} sagax decurrere nôrunt.</l>
   <l>Ventilat iste faces, restinguit at illa furentes</l>
   <l>Taedas. Ne<gap reason="illegible" resp="#tech" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap> taedet Pueri sic taedia caeci</l>
   <l>Fallere, qui caecis conuoluit viscera flammis,</l>
   <l>Ergo refer grates qui deuitare cupi'sti</l>
   <l>Spumosos Veneris fluctus, scopulos{que} minaces</l>
   <l>Qui fragilem tumidis cymbam mersisse procellis</l>
   <l>Possent. Hàc iter est, hàc dirige, tutior ibis.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>Richardus Portingtonus.</signed>
   </closer>
